**Objective: To be able to customise each automatically-configured environment.**

**Software:**

**Puppet, Vagrant, Jenkins**

**What you will learn:**

- Utilizing Environment variables to manage multiple environments

**Instructions to install Jenkins plugins needed for the exercise**

1. Start up the build machine so that we can see the Jenkins home page

d:

cd \workshops\workshop1

vagrant up

1. Go to Jenkins home page by visiting http://localhost:8080
2. Go to "Manage Jenkins"
3. Go to "Manage plugins"
4. Go to "Available" tab
5. Find and install "EnvInject plugin" from list of available plugins

**Instructions to create a job for deployment to staging**

1. Click on "New Item" on the left nav bar.
2. Name the job as "deploy\_to\_staging"
3. Choose "Build a free-style software project"
4. Click "Ok"
5. You should be on job configuration page
6. Check "Prepare an environment for the run"
7. In the "Properties Content" add new port on which app needs to be run by typing APP\_PORT=7070 and BUILD\_ID=dontKillMe, which ensures that Jenkins won't kill off processes spawned as a result of a job

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. In the Source Control Management section select Git.
2. Add your github repository url that you created in previous exercise. https://github.com/your\_name/cd\_linux.git

 

1. Go to Build section and click "Add build step"
2. Select Invoke ant and specify the build target as "run"

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. Save the configuration
2. Go to home page. You should see 2 jobs on the dashboard
3. Run the job "deploy\_to\_staging" and you should be able to see the app on http://localhost:7070/time
